milestones.description: Atapattu and Russel Arnold's 133-run partnership is SL's highest for the 6th wicket in ODIs, breaking the record of 132 between Ranatunga and Ruwan Kalpage

stories.title: '6-1 is not a pretty sight' - Moody
stories.subTitle: India v Sri Lanka, 7th ODI, Baroda
stories.summary: Tom Moody was disappointed with Sri Lanka's overall performance in the series but was confident that they could bounce back pretty soon. He spoke to the media after the game.

stories.title: 'I knew we were onto something special' - Dravid
stories.subTitle: India v Sri Lanka, 7th ODI, Baroda
stories.summary: 'The confidence has been high and a number of youngsters have come through and performed ' - Rahul Dravid

stories.title: Back to big time
stories.subTitle: Sri Lanka in India, ODI series, 2005-06
stories.summary: If not for Sri Lanka resembling boxing's Bum of the Month by the end of a series in which a succession of blows had reduced them to a glassy-eyed stupor, this would have been a euphoric occasion
